                  </hi>. I am the wife of Matthew Moriarty. The prisoner came to my house on a Monday—I do not know the day of the month—he</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183509210177"></xptr>
               <p>had a lodging, and paid 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for it—I went out to work the next day, and I afterwards missed this sheet—I know it to be mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350921-name-1045" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-1045" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-1045" type="surname" value="BALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350921-name-1045" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BALL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 166.) On the 31st of August, I saw the prisoner in the Broadway, Deptford—he went into Mr. Sharp's—I saw him come out, and Mr. Sharp came to the door—I asked him what the prisoner had got—he said a sheet that he suspected he had stolen—I followed the prisoner, and asked what he had got—he said a sheet that he had brough from on board the brig <hi rend="italic">Charlotte;</hi> and that his mother made it him at Kingston, in the West Indies—I took him to the station-house, and the prosecutor owned the sheet.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> The woman where I slept robbed my bundle—I went the next morning, and took this sheet instead of my own—my ship is gone to sea now.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">to</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MARY MORIARTY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did the prisoner leave a sheet behind? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I did not see any—my sheet was clean in a drawer.</p>
